# ViewModel Patterns

## Structure

```kotlin
class FeatureViewModel : ViewModel() {
    val items: StateFlow<List<Item>>
        field = MutableStateFlow(emptyList())

    val isLoading: StateFlow<Boolean>
        field = MutableStateFlow(true)

    init {
        loadData()
    }

    private fun loadData() {
        viewModelScope.launch(Dispatchers.Default) {
            // I/O and processing off main thread
            val result = repository.fetch()
            withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {
                items.value = result
                isLoading.value = false
            }
        }
    }

    override fun onCleared() {
        // Cancel jobs, close clients
        super.onCleared()
    }
}
```

## State exposure

- Expose state as `StateFlow` using the backing-field pattern: `val x: StateFlow<T>  field = MutableStateFlow(initial)`.
- Use `combine()` + `stateIn()` for derived state that depends on multiple flows.
- Use `SharingStarted.Eagerly` when the flow must be active immediately.

## Coroutine discipline

- Launch background work on `Dispatchers.Default`.
- Perform I/O (network, disk) off the main thread.
- Update `MutableStateFlow.value` on `Dispatchers.Main` via `withContext`.
- Always rethrow `CancellationException` — never swallow it.
- Use `supervisorScope` for WebSocket loops so child failures don't cancel the parent.

## Cleanup

- Cancel all running `Job` references in `onCleared()`.
- Close HTTP clients and WebSocket connections to prevent leaks.
- Wrap cleanup in try/catch — ignore errors during teardown.

## Throttling

- Throttle high-frequency updates (e.g., WebSocket tickers) with a time-based gate.
- Debounce user-initiated fetches by cancelling the previous `Job` before launching a new one.
